Program 1: Sorting an Array (Bubble Sort)

Program 1: Sorting an Array (Bubble Sort)

#include <stdio.h>

void bubbleSort(int arr[], int n) {

    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

        for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {

            if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {

                // Swap arr[j] and arr[j+1]

                int temp = arr[j];

                arr[j] = arr[j + 1];

                arr[j + 1] = temp;

            }

        }

    }

}

int main() {

    int arr[] = {64, 34, 25, 12, 22, 11, 90};

    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);

    printf("Original array: ");

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

        printf("%d ", arr[i]);

    }

    // Sort the array using bubble sort

    bubbleSort(arr, n);

    printf("\nSorted array: ");

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

        printf("%d ", arr[i]);

    }

    return 0;

}

In this program, we use the bubble sort algorithm to sort an array in ascending order. We define a bubbleSort function that performs the sorting operation.
